The Police in Taraba State has confirmed the kidnap of the children of the former Commissioner for Justice and Attorney General of the state, Gibon Timothy Kataps by unknown gunmen. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the Command, Usman Abdullahi, who confirmed the kidnap said the children alongside a police officer were snatched on Wednesday afternoon along Jamtari, Gayam road in Gashaka Local Government council of the state. Apart from the kidnapped persons, a villager was also confirmed to have been killed by the hoodlums during the raid which DAILY POST learned lasted for several minutes. The police officer escorting the family of the former Commissioner was said to have sustained guns wounds following the attack. The Command said the Police was working round the clock to rescue the victims and apprehend the perpetrators. Also confirming the incident, the Council Chairman of Gashaka, Paul Dogoh, admitted that he was aware of the ugly development. He said the incident took place at Jamtari, in Gashaka council, and informed that plans to hold an emergency security meeting in the council have been concluded. When reached for confirmation, the former Commissioner in question said six members of his family were kidnapped, namely, his driver, two of his nieces and his children. As at the time of filing this report, the Commissioner said the kidnappers, were yet to reach out to the family to demand ransoms. He appealed to security agencies, to assist the family in rescuing the victims unhurt. Sources from the area also debunked police figures of casualties, saying over five persons lost their lives during the incident.